DOCS
DATA CLOUD
Install the Query Workspaces Package

Download the query workspaces package to Salesforce.

In a new browser tab, open AppExchange.
Search for and open Query Workspaces.
Follow the instructions to install a package.

After installing the query workspaces package, set up the query workspaces to connect to Data Cloud.

Assign Permission Sets to a Query Workspace User
Assign the query workspaces permission set to a user. This permission set allows them to write queries for data model objects, data lake objects, and calculated insights in a query workspace.
Create a Connected App for Query Workspaces
You can use a connected app to connect a query workspace to Data Cloud.
Create an Auth Provider for Query Workspaces
Add an auth provider credential in Salesforce to create a secure connection and access Data Cloud through API integrations.
Create a Named Credential for Query Workspaces
Add a named credential using auth provider information to create a secure connection in Data Cloud. A named credential specifies the URL of a callout endpoint and its required authentication parameters. You can create multiple named credentials to connect to different orgs in Data Cloud.
Create a CSP Trusted Site for Query Workspaces
Add a Content Security Policy (CSP) trusted site to each Data Cloud URL to access query workspaces. CSP defines rules to control the source of content that can be loaded on a page.
Configure a Salesforce CORS Allowed List for Query Workspaces
Add a requesting origin to the Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) allowed list for a Data Cloud org. It allows query workspace resources to connect to connected apps and supported Salesforce APIs from JavaScript code in a web browser.
